  "question_id": "ffb70f78-eeb8-4158-9f4a-b67bc3dc8542",
  "short_text": "Right Angled Triangle - 10",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\n\n```\n*\n* * *\n* * * * *\n* * * * * * *\n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n- Each row should contain odd number of stars (`*`) starting from **1**.\n- There is a space after every star (`*`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows, each row containing an odd number of stars (`*`) as a **Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 3`,\n\n- Print the stars (`*`) in **3** rows as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-right-angled-triangle-10.png' widthPercent='70'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image, the Star in box indicates the star and a space (\"\\* \").\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n*\n* * *\n* * * * *\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "80009fd6-bb72-4fe9-b190-ee0ca2bf2968",
      "code_content": "number_of_rows = int(input())\n\nstars = 1\n\nfor row in range(number_of_rows):\n    each_row = \"* \" * stars\n    stars = stars + 2\n    \n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
